WEBVTT

00:02.102 --> 00:03.536
<i>[jazzy music]</i>

00:03.602 --> 00:05.071
<i>- ♪ Timmy's</i>
<i>still an average kid ♪</i>

00:05.138 --> 00:07.340
<i>♪ That no one understands ♪</i>

00:07.407 --> 00:09.442
<i>♪ Chloe's his new neighbor ♪</i>

00:09.509 --> 00:11.878
<i>♪ And she's ruining</i>
<i>all his plans ♪</i>

00:11.945 --> 00:12.912
- Ahh!

00:12.979 --> 00:13.913
<i>- ♪ All the wishes ♪</i>

00:13.980 --> 00:15.081
<i>♪ In the world ♪</i>

00:15.148 --> 00:17.250
<i>♪ So why should he care? ♪</i>

00:17.317 --> 00:19.552
<i>♪ Jorgen has reported</i>
<i>there's a fairy shortage ♪</i>

00:19.619 --> 00:21.755
<i>♪ So Timmy has to share ♪</i>

00:21.821 --> 00:24.758
<i>♪ His OddParents,</i>
<i>fairly OddParents ♪</i>

00:24.824 --> 00:27.260
- More than one?
- This should be fun!

00:27.327 --> 00:29.229
<i>- ♪ OddParents,</i>
<i>fairly OddParents ♪</i>

00:29.295 --> 00:32.232
<i>♪ Feather suit, nature boots,</i>
<i>laser shooting, rescue ♪</i>

00:32.298 --> 00:33.466
- World peace, kale treats,

00:33.533 --> 00:34.667
bunny feet, real neat!

00:34.734 --> 00:35.802
- What? No!
Leave me alone!

00:35.869 --> 00:38.438
My fairies!
Get your own!

00:38.505 --> 00:40.807
-<i> ♪ OddParents,</i>
<i>fairly OddParents ♪</i>

00:40.874 --> 00:42.776
<i>♪ Timmy, beware,</i>
<i>you'll have to share ♪</i>

00:42.842 --> 00:44.711
{\an8}<i>♪ Your fairly OddParents ♪</i>

00:44.778 --> 00:45.745
{\an8}- Yeah, right!

00:49.716 --> 00:52.652
{\an8}<i>[swinging music]</i>

00:52.719 --> 00:58.825
{\an8}<i>♪</i> ♪

00:58.892 --> 01:00.493
<i>[bell ringing]</i>

01:00.560 --> 01:03.663
[all cheering]

01:03.730 --> 01:06.766
- Spring break!
The happiest time of year!

01:06.833 --> 01:09.235
No, kids, and
the Easter Bunny's coming.

01:09.302 --> 01:12.105
Hippity hoppity--gah!
My hippity! [winces]

01:12.172 --> 01:14.908
Now I have to hoppity.
[groans]

01:14.974 --> 01:16.676
- I'm so excited.

01:16.743 --> 01:19.612
My parents and I are going
camping the Carmichael way.

01:19.679 --> 01:21.681
{\an3}It's an environmentally-correct
adventure

01:21.748 --> 01:24.250
{\an3}where we eat berries and grubs
and drift off to sleep

01:24.317 --> 01:26.653
{\an3}to the sounds of the animals
hunting each other in the night.

01:26.719 --> 01:28.988
{\an1}- Uh, is that a vacation,
or a punishment?

01:29.055 --> 01:30.757
- My ride's here!
[donkey braying]

01:30.824 --> 01:33.593
- Greetings, future custodians
of Mother Earth.

01:33.660 --> 01:34.994
- Weirdo parents alert.

01:35.061 --> 01:37.797
And they're on a donkey.
They never disappoint.

01:37.864 --> 01:39.032
- Oh, this is Eco,

01:39.098 --> 01:41.167
our sustainable mode of
transportation.

01:41.234 --> 01:42.969
He's environmentally friendly,

01:43.036 --> 01:45.738
but not so personally friendly.

01:45.805 --> 01:47.707
- My family's going camping too.

01:47.774 --> 01:49.976
And here's my ride.

01:50.043 --> 01:50.977
[engine roaring]

01:51.044 --> 01:53.613
[horn blaring]

01:53.680 --> 01:56.616
<i>[jazzy music]</i>

01:56.683 --> 02:00.787
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:00.854 --> 02:02.355
- Oh, Timmy.

02:02.422 --> 02:04.657
{\an3}I hope you're ready to hit
the great outdoors,

02:04.724 --> 02:08.094
because I've been hitting
everything with my new RV.

02:08.161 --> 02:10.295
- What is that monstrosity?

02:10.363 --> 02:11.865
It's like a house on wheels.

02:11.931 --> 02:14.567
- Well, that's because it is
a house on wheels.

02:14.634 --> 02:17.670
When my family goes camping,
we don't like to go outside.

02:17.737 --> 02:20.640
{\an3}- Timmy, what are you doing
outside? Hop in!

02:20.707 --> 02:23.543
{\an3}You can be the first one
to test out the bowling alley.

02:23.610 --> 02:25.812
- We have a pool boy!

02:25.879 --> 02:27.013
- Ah!

02:27.080 --> 02:28.681
{\an1}- How's Timmy
going to enjoy nature

02:28.748 --> 02:30.383
being cooped up in that thing?

02:30.450 --> 02:32.685
{\an3}- How 'bout we go find out and
we'll let you know, okay?

02:32.752 --> 02:33.887
See you. Enjoy the grubs.

02:33.953 --> 02:36.723
{\an1}- Hurry!
They have a pool boy!

02:36.789 --> 02:38.525
[horn blaring]

02:38.591 --> 02:41.528
- [laughing]

02:41.594 --> 02:43.396
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:43.463 --> 02:46.432
- Whoo-hoo!
I'm flying with popcorn!

02:46.499 --> 02:47.800
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:47.867 --> 02:48.801
Mmm!

02:48.868 --> 02:49.969
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:50.036 --> 02:51.938
- Mmm!
- Ah!

02:52.005 --> 02:54.274
[shouting]

02:54.340 --> 02:57.043
{\an3}- Hey Chloe, my house on wheels
has a combo

02:57.110 --> 02:59.412
sky-diving simulator/
kettle corn machine!

02:59.479 --> 03:01.347
{\an3}Does your donkey
come with anything?

03:01.414 --> 03:03.349
{\an1}- It comes with its own
fly swatter,

03:03.416 --> 03:05.118
{\an1}which is handy because of
all the flies.

03:05.184 --> 03:06.619
I miss you and the fairies!

03:06.686 --> 03:09.556
- We miss you too!
But we've got kettle corn.

03:09.622 --> 03:12.792
{\an1}- I know.
What if we go camping together?

03:12.859 --> 03:15.628
- Sure, as long as I don't
have to actually camp.

03:15.695 --> 03:17.130
- Ooh. Cosmo. Wanda.

03:17.196 --> 03:19.866
{\an1}I wish that no matter where
our parents take us,

03:19.933 --> 03:22.001
{\an1}Timmy and I always
end up together.

03:22.068 --> 03:23.369
<i>[dinging]</i>

03:23.436 --> 03:26.573
<i>[swinging music]</i>

03:26.639 --> 03:29.576
{\an8}<i>[country music]</i>

03:29.642 --> 03:35.648
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:35.715 --> 03:37.684
- Hmm? Ah!

03:37.750 --> 03:39.319
Ooh!

03:39.385 --> 03:41.287
- Hey, Clampickles.

03:41.354 --> 03:43.122
Fancy meeting you here.

03:43.189 --> 03:44.691
Well, we have camping to do,

03:44.757 --> 03:47.727
{\an3}so we're gonna head inside,
away from icky nature.

03:47.794 --> 03:49.329
{\an3}- Oh, hey, Chloe,
I was swimming

03:49.395 --> 03:50.897
{\an3}with dolphins
in the aquatic center.

03:50.964 --> 03:52.332
Here, have an éclair.

03:52.398 --> 03:54.634
{\an3}Our French pastry chef
made them.

03:54.701 --> 03:56.102
{\an1}- Thank you for the éclair,
Timmy,

03:56.169 --> 03:58.771
{\an1}but I filled up on grubs
during the ride in.

03:58.838 --> 04:02.208
{\an1}Then again, I don't
want to be rude.

04:02.275 --> 04:04.644
{\an3}- [grunts]

04:04.711 --> 04:06.179
- Ah, look at us.

04:06.245 --> 04:09.282
Thanks to Chloe's wish,
we're all camping together.

04:09.349 --> 04:11.351
Well, I have to go back inside.

04:11.417 --> 04:14.554
The pool boy's leading
an aqua fitness class.

04:14.621 --> 04:16.689
- Eh, I'm not going
back in there.

04:16.755 --> 04:19.826
I got roughed up pretty bad
in the kettle corn machine.

04:19.892 --> 04:21.461
I'm safer out here.

04:21.527 --> 04:22.295
{\an3}Oh!

04:22.362 --> 04:24.130
- Ooh, a bocce ball.

04:24.197 --> 04:25.865
- I need another eye patch!

04:28.234 --> 04:30.603
- Wienergristles? Ha!

04:30.670 --> 04:32.338
That's the greatest name
I've heard

04:32.405 --> 04:34.440
since our old neighbors
the Fartbarfs.

04:34.507 --> 04:36.409
{\an3}- The Wienergristles are our
magical elf friends

04:36.476 --> 04:38.444
who live in a cookie forest and
are clinically

04:38.511 --> 04:40.313
obsessed with bocce ball.

04:40.380 --> 04:42.315
I'd love to see them.
Ah!

04:42.382 --> 04:44.250
In fact,
I'd love to see anything.

04:44.317 --> 04:46.219
- Magical forest elves?

04:46.285 --> 04:47.687
I've always believed in them.

04:47.754 --> 04:49.122
I told my parents
they were real,

04:49.188 --> 04:51.057
but they sent me
to the talking doctor.

04:51.124 --> 04:53.292
Dr. Moskowitz was wrong!

04:53.359 --> 04:55.795
{\an3}- Elves with an awesome name
and cookies?

04:55.862 --> 04:57.263
I am so there.

04:57.330 --> 04:59.198
{\an8}<i>[dinging]</i>

04:59.265 --> 05:02.201
<i>[majestic harp music]</i>

05:02.268 --> 05:04.203
Cookies growing on trees?

05:04.270 --> 05:06.072
I love nature now.

05:06.139 --> 05:07.473
[chomping] Mmm.

05:07.540 --> 05:09.509
- I knew cookie trees were real.

05:09.575 --> 05:12.979
Dr. Moskowitz was wrong
about so many things.

05:13.046 --> 05:14.013
Ah!

05:14.080 --> 05:15.448
- Welcome, Welcome, everyone.

05:15.515 --> 05:17.383
Come on in and have some fun.

05:17.450 --> 05:19.352
- We're Mo and Mindy
Wienergristle.

05:19.419 --> 05:21.954
We like to sing
and sometimes whistle.

05:22.021 --> 05:23.723
- Elves talk in rhymes?

05:23.790 --> 05:24.924
{\an1}I knew it.

05:24.991 --> 05:27.226
- Yeah, I kind of
forgot about that.

05:27.293 --> 05:28.795
It gets a little old.

05:28.861 --> 05:30.730
- Yes, indeed.
So we've been told.

05:30.797 --> 05:33.032
- Ooh, is that a chocolate
waterfall?

05:33.099 --> 05:35.334
I love nature.

05:35.401 --> 05:36.335
- Be right there.

05:36.402 --> 05:37.970
I am composing a spirited

05:38.037 --> 05:39.706
rebuttal to Dr. Moskowitz.

05:39.772 --> 05:42.842
"Dear closed-minded quack..."

05:42.909 --> 05:44.477
- Good neighbors. Hello.

05:44.544 --> 05:46.279
Would you be so kind
as to turn off

05:46.345 --> 05:48.681
your carbon-spewing,
ozone-depleting engine?

05:48.748 --> 05:51.184
<i>- Oh, sorry, Mrs. Crabpincher.</i>

05:51.250 --> 05:53.119
<i>I got the premium-package RV.</i>

05:53.186 --> 05:54.654
<i>It never turns off!</i>

05:54.721 --> 05:57.156
- All righty, I'm just gonna do
my very best, then,

05:57.223 --> 05:58.658
to respect your differentness.

05:58.725 --> 06:00.760
<i>- Whatever floats your boat,</i>
<i>Mrs. Cubicle.</i>

06:00.827 --> 06:02.695
<i>Honey, rev up</i>
<i>the pollution machine.</i>

06:02.762 --> 06:05.698
{\an3}<i>The gentle hum drowns out the</i>
<i>hideous sounds of nature.</i>

06:05.765 --> 06:08.735
{\an1}- Find your bliss, honey.
Deep breaths.

06:08.801 --> 06:11.337
- [deep breaths]

06:11.404 --> 06:13.139
[coughing]

06:13.206 --> 06:14.540
I'm a little rattled.

06:14.607 --> 06:17.009
{\an3}I need to chant
my happy place mantra.

06:17.076 --> 06:19.812
<i>[dreamy Eastern music]</i>

06:19.879 --> 06:21.547
I'm where I'm supposed to be.

06:21.614 --> 06:23.483
I'm safe in my space.

06:23.549 --> 06:25.451
{\an1}- Ooh, looks like
the premium package

06:25.518 --> 06:27.653
didn't come with a trash can.

06:30.490 --> 06:32.558
- I hate them because
they don't recycle!

06:32.625 --> 06:34.160
- That's a weird mantra, Connie.

06:34.227 --> 06:35.895
- It's not a mantra!

06:35.962 --> 06:38.898
- Keep it down, hippies!

06:38.965 --> 06:42.335
- [laughing]

06:42.401 --> 06:43.836
Check this out: I'm dipping

06:43.903 --> 06:47.039
{\an1}a marshmallow cloud
in the chocolate waterfall.

06:47.106 --> 06:49.876
[loud chomping]

06:49.942 --> 06:51.410
{\an3}- Don't tell my parents,
but this is

06:51.477 --> 06:54.714
so much better than grubs!

06:56.015 --> 06:57.517
both: Our ball is in
the perfect place.

06:57.583 --> 06:59.852
Ha ha ha, and in your face.

06:59.919 --> 07:02.922
{\an3}- You guys take bocce ball
pretty seriously.

07:02.989 --> 07:04.157
It's kind of sad.

07:04.223 --> 07:05.358
- I got this, Wanda.

07:05.424 --> 07:07.393
I'm assuming you're still here.

07:07.460 --> 07:10.263
[grunting]

07:10.329 --> 07:12.064
{\an3}Did we win?

07:12.131 --> 07:14.200
- You people are garbage people.

07:14.267 --> 07:15.601
That's what you are.

07:15.668 --> 07:17.236
And Clark would agree with me

07:17.303 --> 07:18.838
if he were conscious right now.

07:18.905 --> 07:21.073
{\an3}- Hey, honey.
I need a snappy comeback.

07:21.140 --> 07:22.408
- [whispering]

07:22.475 --> 07:25.611
both:
♪ Nah, nah, nah, nah, nah ♪

07:25.678 --> 07:28.181
- Hey, why are
you guys fighting?

07:28.247 --> 07:30.082
- Oh, we're not fighting.
We're leaving.

07:30.149 --> 07:32.952
Come on, Chloe, help me drag
your father to the donkey.

07:33.019 --> 07:34.887
<i>[playful music]</i>

07:34.954 --> 07:36.222
- Bye, Timmy.

07:36.289 --> 07:38.658
I wish we could spend
our vacation together,

07:38.724 --> 07:41.127
but I guess that's not
gonna happen.

07:41.194 --> 07:43.296
Wink, wink.

07:43.362 --> 07:45.965
[donkey braying]

07:46.032 --> 07:53.973
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:56.809 --> 07:58.277
{\an1}- Ah!

07:58.344 --> 07:59.812
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:59.879 --> 08:01.380
{\an1}Eh! Uh?

08:01.447 --> 08:02.615
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:02.682 --> 08:04.283
[screaming nonsense]

08:04.350 --> 08:05.284
<i>♪</i> ♪

08:05.351 --> 08:07.486
Ah! We keep magically ending up

08:07.553 --> 08:09.055
back with the stupid Cowabungas.

08:09.121 --> 08:11.691
{\an3}We're in some kind of woodland
Bermuda Triangle.

08:11.757 --> 08:13.659
- Uh, this is bad karma, Clark.

08:13.726 --> 08:15.928
{\an1}Do you think it's the universe
punishing us

08:15.995 --> 08:18.431
for that night we slipped and
ordered the meat-lovers pizza?

08:18.497 --> 08:19.899
- Could be.
- You know what I think

08:19.966 --> 08:22.401
the universe is really
telling us, guys?

08:22.468 --> 08:24.270
That we're neighbors,
and friends,

08:24.337 --> 08:26.239
and we need to work out
our differences.

08:26.305 --> 08:29.208
- Sorry, sweetie, but that's
a garbage idea!

08:29.275 --> 08:30.877
- It's hippie talk!

08:30.943 --> 08:33.980
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:34.046 --> 08:35.248
- Well, we tried, Chloe.

08:35.313 --> 08:37.582
{\an1}Actually, you tried.
I'm not much of a trier.

08:37.650 --> 08:39.652
{\an3}- It's okay, Timmy.
I'm a try-too-mucher.

08:39.719 --> 08:41.453
We just need to find something

08:41.520 --> 08:42.989
our parents have in common.

08:43.054 --> 08:44.891
- Timmy, come inside!

08:44.957 --> 08:46.192
We miss you!

08:46.259 --> 08:50.229
{\an3}- Chloe, come play a fun
math game with Mommy.

08:50.296 --> 08:51.564
- That's it!

08:51.631 --> 08:53.399
The one thing our parents
have in common

08:53.466 --> 08:54.767
is that they love us.

08:54.834 --> 08:57.270
- Which gives me a crazy idea.

08:57.336 --> 08:59.205
- Oh, Timmy, you're trying.

08:59.272 --> 09:00.806
I'm so proud.

09:00.873 --> 09:01.974
{\an1}- [grunts]

09:02.875 --> 09:04.243
Did we win?
- Yes!

09:04.310 --> 09:06.245
Because the rhyming stopped.

09:06.312 --> 09:07.613
- Wanda! Cosmo!

09:07.680 --> 09:09.248
{\an1}Our parents are fighting,
so we want you

09:09.315 --> 09:10.516
{\an1}to poof into bears
and drag us off

09:10.583 --> 09:12.018
into the woods like
you're gonna eat us.

09:12.084 --> 09:14.620
{\an1}- Because once our parents see
we are in danger,

09:14.687 --> 09:17.490
{\an1}they will bond together
in order to save us.

09:17.556 --> 09:19.425
<i>[playful music]</i>

09:19.492 --> 09:21.727
- You can count on us, guys.

09:21.794 --> 09:23.095
You're still here, right?

09:23.162 --> 09:25.498
Okay. My turn.

09:25.564 --> 09:27.700
both: Ah!

09:28.935 --> 09:31.871
[growling]

09:34.774 --> 09:36.575
- Connie, what are you up to?

09:36.642 --> 09:38.644
You've got the crazy eyes.

09:38.711 --> 09:40.246
- Oh, I'm not Connie anymore.

09:40.313 --> 09:42.014
I'm a vengeful warrior princess.

09:42.081 --> 09:45.051
{\an1}I'm gonna dip my sharpened stick
into frog poison

09:45.117 --> 09:47.720
{\an1}and poke the Turners
until they genuinely apologize

09:47.787 --> 09:49.455
{\an1}for their eco-unfriendly
behavior,

09:49.522 --> 09:52.825
{\an1}and then after that, I'm gonna
order a meat-lovers pizza,

09:52.892 --> 09:55.094
{\an1}because quite frankly,
I've snapped!

09:55.161 --> 09:57.129
{\an3}- Conveniently passing out
again.

09:57.196 --> 09:58.864
{\an3}[groaning]

09:58.931 --> 10:01.767
{\an1}- This is the perfect place
to be mauled by bears.

10:01.834 --> 10:04.036
And here comes Cosmo and Wanda,

10:04.103 --> 10:05.638
right on cue.

10:05.705 --> 10:08.307
[growling]

10:08.374 --> 10:09.308
{\an3}- [gasps]

10:09.375 --> 10:10.609
[growling]

10:10.676 --> 10:11.711
[screaming]

10:11.777 --> 10:13.245
Mommy! Daddy! Help!

10:13.312 --> 10:15.514
I'm being mauled by
a kockadoody bear!

10:15.581 --> 10:17.416
- That's great acting.

10:17.483 --> 10:18.784
Try waving your arms a bit.

10:18.851 --> 10:21.120
- This is not Cosmo and Wanda.

10:21.187 --> 10:22.722
They're real bears!

10:22.788 --> 10:25.725
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

10:25.791 --> 10:29.228
{\an8}- Mommy, Daddy, help!
Real Bears!

10:29.295 --> 10:31.030
- I'll save you, kids.

10:31.097 --> 10:32.798
Oh! Ah!

10:32.865 --> 10:34.200
- Watch out, Mama Bear,

10:34.266 --> 10:36.702
because the other Mama Bear is
in the hizzouse!

10:36.769 --> 10:38.604
And I've got a pointy stick!

10:38.671 --> 10:40.106
- Hang on, Mrs. Claptrap!

10:40.172 --> 10:42.408
{\an3}We've got jet packs
and a bear immobilizer.

10:42.475 --> 10:44.210
{\an3}They came with
the premium package.

10:44.276 --> 10:47.913
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:47.980 --> 10:49.915
all: Don't. Mess. With.

10:49.982 --> 10:51.517
Our. Kids!

10:51.584 --> 10:55.321
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:55.388 --> 10:57.156
[whimpering]

10:57.223 --> 10:59.725
- Yes! My crazy idea worked!

10:59.792 --> 11:02.094
- Thanks to our crazy parents.

11:02.161 --> 11:03.829
<i>[triumphant music]</i>

11:03.896 --> 11:07.566
- [crying]
Those were real bears!

11:07.633 --> 11:10.269
- [crying]
I wasn't acting!

11:10.336 --> 11:13.606
- I know, 'cause you're
a terrible actress.

11:13.672 --> 11:16.409
- ♪ Who wants
a meat-lovers pizza? ♪

11:16.475 --> 11:18.744
- [grumbling]

11:18.811 --> 11:21.947
<i>[swinging music]</i>

11:22.014 --> 11:23.282
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:23.349 --> 11:24.283
[donkey braying]

11:24.350 --> 11:25.284
[dolphin clicking]

11:25.351 --> 11:26.685
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:26.752 --> 11:28.554
- Best spring break ever.

11:28.621 --> 11:29.688
And also the weirdest.

11:29.755 --> 11:31.023
- I'm just glad we're not

11:31.090 --> 11:33.392
with those little rhyming
cookie kooks.

11:33.459 --> 11:35.561
- I'm just happy
I can see again.

11:35.628 --> 11:37.430
Ah! Kettle corn!

11:37.496 --> 11:38.731
[loud chomping]

11:38.798 --> 11:40.499
all: They fought the bears
and made amends,

11:40.566 --> 11:42.468
and now they are
the best of friends.

11:42.535 --> 11:44.537
Ah!
- Still old!

11:44.603 --> 11:46.338
- The Easter Bunny!

11:46.405 --> 11:47.773
{\an8}<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:52.111 --> 11:55.047
{\an8}<i>[wacky music]</i>

11:55.114 --> 12:01.020
{\an8}<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:01.087 --> 12:04.023
<i>[jaunty music]</i>

12:04.090 --> 12:05.491
[lone knock]
- Come in, Timmy!

12:05.558 --> 12:07.293
{\an1}- Hey, Chloe.
Are you ready for--

12:07.359 --> 12:09.261
- Dimmsdale Daze,
the best carnival

12:09.328 --> 12:10.729
in the whole wide world?

12:10.796 --> 12:12.164
Yes!
- Me too!

12:12.231 --> 12:14.400
I can't wait to ride
the Barf Dragon.

12:14.467 --> 12:16.135
It's the world's
sickest roller coaster.

12:16.202 --> 12:17.603
Also, it makes you sick.

12:17.670 --> 12:20.172
{\an7}That's why I brought my own
trusty barf bag.

12:20.239 --> 12:22.475
{\an7}- A barf bag?
Wait, that's what I am?

12:22.541 --> 12:26.445
{\an7}- Uh, what am I, sport?
The bag to hold your candy?

12:26.512 --> 12:28.214
{\an8}- The candy I've already eaten.

12:28.280 --> 12:30.816
{\an9}Because you're my backup
barf bag!

12:30.883 --> 12:34.987
{\an3}- Ha ha, Wanda.
I'm Timmy's favorite barf bag.

12:35.054 --> 12:36.956
No, wait--
- Oh, Chloe!

12:37.022 --> 12:39.291
[yelling like Tarzan]

12:39.358 --> 12:40.626
- We've been making vines like

12:40.693 --> 12:42.661
all the cool kids are doing
these days.

12:42.728 --> 12:45.865
{\an7}- Okay, that's the wrong kind
of, uh...

12:45.931 --> 12:47.266
{\an7}Never mind.
Good try.

12:47.333 --> 12:50.202
{\an7}- Mommy, Daddy, I'm going
to Dimmsdale Daze.

12:50.269 --> 12:52.671
{\an7}I'm gonna throw up on
the Barf Dragon with Timmy.

12:52.738 --> 12:54.940
{\an8}- Well, doesn't that
sound unproductive.

12:55.007 --> 12:56.742
{\an7}Sorry, but it's out
of the question.

12:56.809 --> 12:59.145
{\an8}You see, carnivals are
an offense to humanity

12:59.211 --> 13:01.080
{\an8}with their deep-fried
garbage food,

13:01.147 --> 13:03.349
{\an8}shyster game booths,
and worst of all,

13:03.415 --> 13:06.685
{\an8}scary carnies, who I am pretty
darn sure do not recycle.

13:06.752 --> 13:08.420
{\an3}- Besides, your mother and I
have already

13:08.487 --> 13:10.523
made some fun family plans.

13:10.589 --> 13:12.358
{\an3}We're gonna chain ourselves to
the old elm tree

13:12.424 --> 13:14.393
in the town square
so evil developers

13:14.460 --> 13:15.728
can't cut it down.

13:15.794 --> 13:17.630
That should make for
a snazzy time, huh?

13:17.696 --> 13:19.598
{\an8}- Plus, a picture of us
chained to the tree

13:19.665 --> 13:22.134
{\an8}will make an absolutely boffo
Christmas card.

13:22.201 --> 13:23.536
{\an8}That we can recycle.

13:23.602 --> 13:25.771
{\an8}- But I want to go
to Dimmsdale Daze.

13:25.838 --> 13:28.374
{\an8}- Well, when you're a parent,
you can make your own decisions.

13:28.440 --> 13:29.975
{\an8}But we know what's best for you,

13:30.042 --> 13:31.777
{\an8}Chloe Jonas Salk Mandela
Carmichael.

13:31.844 --> 13:34.980
{\an8}And that's chaining yourself
to a tree.

13:35.047 --> 13:36.782
{\an8}- Ooh, just once I wish

13:36.849 --> 13:38.484
I could be the parent
so I could

13:38.551 --> 13:40.519
do what I want and go
to the carnival.

13:40.586 --> 13:42.421
- Wish granted.
You're a parent

13:42.488 --> 13:45.457
for as long as Dimmsdale Daze
is in town.

13:45.524 --> 13:48.260
{\an8}<i>[triumphant trumpet music]</i>

13:48.327 --> 13:50.863
- I'm a parent!
I'm in charge!

13:50.930 --> 13:52.765
{\an3}On the downside,
I'm wearing mom jeans.

13:52.831 --> 13:54.967
- And Cosmo and Wanda
disappeared.

13:55.034 --> 13:56.602
I'm out two barf bags.

13:56.669 --> 13:59.939
{\an3}- Hey Chloe, rocking
those mom jeans.

14:00.005 --> 14:02.141
Also, Cosmo and Wanda are gone

14:02.208 --> 14:03.642
{\an3}because by wishing
to be an adult,

14:03.709 --> 14:05.911
{\an3}you are now too old
to have fairies.

14:05.978 --> 14:09.148
{\an3}And since you and Timmy are on
a fairy-share scenario,

14:09.215 --> 14:10.916
{\an3}he is squat out of luck
as well!

14:10.983 --> 14:13.419
{\an3}Well, I'm off to get in line
for the Barf Dragon.

14:13.485 --> 14:16.855
{\an3}You do not want to be
on that ride late in the day.

14:16.922 --> 14:18.958
{\an3}- Timmy, I just thought
of something.

14:19.024 --> 14:22.828
{\an3}If I'm a parent, then my parents
must be my...

14:22.895 --> 14:24.263
both: Mommy! Mommy!

14:24.330 --> 14:27.733
- Mommy, Clark flushed my Sunday
shoes down the toilet.

14:27.800 --> 14:29.068
It was awesome.

14:29.134 --> 14:30.903
- And Connie shaved off
my eyebrows.

14:30.970 --> 14:32.905
It was great.

14:32.972 --> 14:34.306
- [laughing]

14:34.373 --> 14:37.109
I'm not mad at your
age-appropriate whimsy.

14:37.176 --> 14:39.044
Because unlike my mom and dad,

14:39.111 --> 14:40.613
I'm a fun parent.

14:40.679 --> 14:42.615
- Your kids are
my kind of people.

14:42.681 --> 14:45.451
Dimmsdale Daze, here we come.

14:45.517 --> 14:47.319
- [grunts]
Ah!

14:47.386 --> 14:50.022
{\an1}- I got to say, Chloe,
for your first time driving,

14:50.089 --> 14:52.224
{\an1}you're way worse than
I thought you'd be.

14:52.291 --> 14:53.792
both: Are we there yet?
Are we there yet?

14:53.859 --> 14:56.895
Are we there yet?
- Soon, valued offspring.

14:56.962 --> 14:58.864
[grunts]
'Cause I'm taking a shortcut.

14:58.931 --> 15:02.067
I'm a parent, and I get
to do what I want.

15:02.134 --> 15:04.003
Yahoo!

15:04.069 --> 15:05.471
<i>[rock music]</i>

15:05.537 --> 15:07.106
We're there.

15:07.172 --> 15:10.276
[children cheering]

15:10.342 --> 15:12.544
[child barfing]
- Did you hear that?

15:12.611 --> 15:14.013
That's the sound of a kid

15:14.079 --> 15:16.448
{\an1}coughing up
a deep-fried corn dog.

15:16.515 --> 15:17.850
We must be near...

15:17.916 --> 15:20.119
all: The Barf Dragon!

15:20.185 --> 15:22.788
[all cheering]

15:22.855 --> 15:26.025
- Sorry, ma'am.
Front cars are for kids.

15:26.091 --> 15:29.962
You got to ride in the back with
the other creepy adults.

15:30.029 --> 15:31.797
- Strap in, fellow creepy adult.

15:31.864 --> 15:34.900
{\an3}BT Dubs, way to rock
those mom jeans.

15:34.967 --> 15:38.237
Oh, this must be your first time
in the dragon's caboose.

15:38.304 --> 15:40.072
{\an1}- What?
Why did you say those words?

15:40.139 --> 15:42.107
- 'Cause you don't have
a barf shield.

15:42.174 --> 15:44.009
Ha ha!
[kids cheering]

15:44.076 --> 15:46.078
Come at me, chunks!

15:46.145 --> 15:49.682
[all cheering]

15:49.748 --> 15:51.984
- Hey, guys.
I don't stink anymore.

15:52.051 --> 15:55.087
I got hosed down by the guy who
washes the elephants.

15:55.154 --> 15:57.056
all: Yay!
- Yay!

15:57.122 --> 16:00.392
I'm doing what I want
'cause I'm the parent.

16:00.459 --> 16:02.861
I'm never going
on the Barf Dragon again.

16:02.928 --> 16:04.763
- Creepy adult alert!

16:04.830 --> 16:06.965
Bounce her out!

16:07.032 --> 16:08.934
- Ah!

16:09.001 --> 16:12.004
{\an1}- Wow, lady, you are a glutton
for punishment.

16:12.071 --> 16:13.872
{\an3}- Ah!

16:13.939 --> 16:15.307
Ah...

16:15.374 --> 16:17.376
{\an1}- Hey, Chloe, we bought
one of everything

16:17.443 --> 16:19.078
from the deep-fried
everything booth.

16:19.144 --> 16:22.414
I have no idea what I'm eating,
but it's delicious.

16:22.481 --> 16:24.883
{\an3}- Clark and I ate 11 pounds
of cotton candy.

16:24.950 --> 16:26.852
{\an3}Can we have more?
Please, please, please, please,

16:26.919 --> 16:28.487
{\an3}please, please, please,
please, please?

16:28.554 --> 16:30.189
- Yes. Fine. Here.

16:30.255 --> 16:32.057
both: You're the best mom ever.

16:32.124 --> 16:35.627
- Well, I've had a wonderful
time at Dimmsdale Daze.

16:35.694 --> 16:37.162
Although, a lot of people have
thrown up on me,

16:37.229 --> 16:40.065
and the elastic on my mom jeans
is starting to pinch.

16:40.132 --> 16:42.034
{\an3}- Yeah, yeah, yeah,
but it's time to check out

16:42.101 --> 16:44.370
{\an3}the most awesome attraction
of all:

16:44.436 --> 16:46.271
Carney Alley.

16:46.338 --> 16:48.774
<i>[scary laughter]</i>

16:48.841 --> 16:50.709
It's not an official attraction.

16:50.776 --> 16:52.711
It's where all the cool carnies
take their breaks.

16:52.778 --> 16:55.647
You'll see things in Carney
Alley you'll never forget,

16:55.714 --> 16:56.982
even if you want to.

16:57.049 --> 16:59.051
- But my mom,
who's now my daughter,

16:59.118 --> 17:00.819
says that carnies are scary.

17:00.886 --> 17:02.221
- That's what makes them fun.

17:02.287 --> 17:03.889
{\an1}Last year, a guy named
Lazy Eye Larry

17:03.956 --> 17:05.691
{\an1}paid me 70 bucks to crawl
through a doggy door

17:05.758 --> 17:07.593
{\an1}and get his ex-fiancé's
engagement ring back.

17:07.659 --> 17:09.127
- Can we go?
Can we go to Carney Alley?

17:09.194 --> 17:11.096
Please, please, please, please,
please, please, please,

17:11.163 --> 17:12.397
please, please, please?

17:12.464 --> 17:14.532
- Fun parent, fun parent,
fun parent.

17:14.599 --> 17:17.069
Uh, you betcha?
- Yes!

17:17.136 --> 17:19.037
- I'd like to see Lazy Eye Larry
again,

17:19.104 --> 17:20.772
but word on the street
is that he's working

17:20.839 --> 17:24.343
a new ride called the
Witness Protection Program.

17:24.410 --> 17:26.111
<i>[growling]</i>
<i>- Ah!</i>

17:26.178 --> 17:28.247
[all screaming]

17:28.313 --> 17:30.416
Was that a lizard or a man?

17:30.482 --> 17:32.084
- Could have been both.

17:32.151 --> 17:35.087
It's Carney Alley.

17:35.154 --> 17:37.022
- Ah!
I mean, whoopee!

17:37.089 --> 17:38.323
Ha, said the fun mom.

17:38.390 --> 17:40.459
{\an1}But oh rats,
we have to go home now

17:40.526 --> 17:42.194
{\an1}because we're
all out of tickets.

17:42.261 --> 17:44.696
[laughing]
- Oh, Timmy!

17:44.763 --> 17:47.199
I've got a gazillion tickets.

17:47.266 --> 17:50.469
- No! No, no, no, no, no!

17:50.536 --> 17:51.603
I mean, whoopee.

17:51.670 --> 17:53.105
[all cheering]

17:53.172 --> 17:54.940
{\an1}- It's actually more
than a gazillion.

17:55.007 --> 17:57.075
{\an1}It's a googolplex of tickets,
which, like seven,

17:57.142 --> 17:59.445
{\an1}is a number too big
for me to understand.

17:59.511 --> 18:01.713
- Okay, I'll go on
one more ride,

18:01.780 --> 18:03.715
as long as it's not
the Gravitwist.

18:03.782 --> 18:05.617
- But the Gravitwist is fun.

18:05.684 --> 18:08.120
{\an3}- And we thought you were
a fun mom.

18:08.187 --> 18:09.888
{\an1}- [sighs]

18:09.955 --> 18:12.591
[all cheering]

18:12.658 --> 18:14.326
I hope this is a short ride.

18:14.393 --> 18:15.894
- It is, but no worries.

18:15.961 --> 18:18.063
{\an1}I gave the ride operate
all my tickets,

18:18.130 --> 18:20.365
{\an1}so we're gonna get a googolplex
of turns,

18:20.432 --> 18:22.734
{\an1}which is a long time
in human years.

18:22.801 --> 18:23.969
<i>[playful carnival music]</i>

18:24.036 --> 18:27.005
[all cheering]

18:27.072 --> 18:28.774
- [screaming]

18:28.841 --> 18:31.977
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:32.044 --> 18:34.780
- Whoa, I think we went back in
time there for a minute.

18:34.847 --> 18:37.282
I saw Ben Franklin
riding a dinosaur.

18:37.349 --> 18:39.618
- I'm saying this as a fun mom.

18:39.685 --> 18:42.521
I hated that ride!

18:43.655 --> 18:45.123
Well, we're home.

18:45.190 --> 18:47.092
{\an3}Mommy's gonna sleep until this
whole nightmare--

18:47.159 --> 18:49.528
{\an3}I mean, super fun experience--
is over.

18:49.595 --> 18:50.729
So night, night.

18:50.796 --> 18:52.564
- Sleep-over! Sleep-over!

18:52.631 --> 18:54.466
all: Sleep-over! Sleep-over!

18:54.533 --> 18:56.401
Sleep-over!
- Okay.

18:56.468 --> 18:57.836
You guys can have a sleepover.

18:57.903 --> 19:00.072
{\an3}As long as you promise
not to bother Mommy.

19:00.138 --> 19:03.509
- Eh, but we're kids.
We need parental guidance.

19:03.575 --> 19:05.077
- I thought you were
a creepy adult.

19:05.143 --> 19:07.479
- But I have the mind
of a child.

19:07.546 --> 19:08.914
- It's true. He's been tested.

19:08.981 --> 19:13.519
{\an3}- Okay, I am the fun mom,
so sleepover it is.

19:13.585 --> 19:16.021
{\an3}But "Sleepover" has the word
"sleep" in it,

19:16.088 --> 19:17.489
so go to sleep!

19:17.556 --> 19:21.326
[crying]

19:21.393 --> 19:22.561
[loud booming]
Ah!

19:22.628 --> 19:24.930
What did you do?

19:24.997 --> 19:25.731
Ah!

19:25.797 --> 19:27.165
- We made popcorn.

19:27.232 --> 19:29.368
- A googolplex of it.

19:29.434 --> 19:31.069
- Tell us a story, Fun Mom.

19:31.136 --> 19:32.738
- But I'm so tired.

19:32.804 --> 19:35.507
both: Sto-ry! Sto-ry! Sto-ry!

19:35.574 --> 19:37.009
- Once upon a time!

19:37.075 --> 19:39.177
There was a girl who wanted
to be a parent

19:39.244 --> 19:40.913
so she could do
what she wanted to do.

19:40.979 --> 19:42.381
She tried to be a fun mom,

19:42.447 --> 19:44.316
but she got stuck in
the dragon's caboose--

19:44.383 --> 19:46.985
- This story's stupid!
- Without a barf shield.

19:47.052 --> 19:48.787
And she was dragged
into Carney Alley

19:48.854 --> 19:51.156
where she saw things
she can never un-see.

19:51.223 --> 19:52.758
The end! Nighty night!

19:52.824 --> 19:55.494
- That was a scary story.
- And stupid.

19:55.561 --> 19:58.163
- Now we need a happy story
so that we can go to sleep

19:58.230 --> 20:00.432
and rest up for another
fun-filled day

20:00.499 --> 20:01.767
at Dimmsdale Daze.

20:01.833 --> 20:04.970
all: Dimmsdale Daze!
Dimmsdale Daze!

20:05.037 --> 20:07.472
- No!
No more Dimmsdale Daze

20:07.539 --> 20:09.508
for you, you little monsters!

20:09.575 --> 20:12.344
Not tomorrow, not ever!

20:12.411 --> 20:14.746
You are monster children

20:14.813 --> 20:17.549
with evil in your hearts.

20:17.616 --> 20:21.520
- [sobbing]

20:21.587 --> 20:23.555
{\an3}- Monsters!

20:23.622 --> 20:25.924
{\an1}- Wow, that was
some terrible parenting.

20:25.991 --> 20:27.626
Who wants to play with knives?

20:27.693 --> 20:29.094
both: Me!

20:29.161 --> 20:31.597
<i>[serene music]</i>

20:31.663 --> 20:33.832
<i>[distant cheering]</i>
- [yawning]

20:33.899 --> 20:36.335
Those kids have
driven me nanners.

20:36.401 --> 20:39.571
It sounds like Dimmsdale Daze
is right outside my house.

20:39.638 --> 20:40.572
Oh!

20:40.639 --> 20:42.507
Ah! Ah!

20:42.574 --> 20:43.508
[all cheering]

20:43.575 --> 20:45.177
What in the name of Carney Alley

20:45.243 --> 20:46.645
is going on here?

20:46.712 --> 20:48.814
{\an3}- Well you wouldn't let us go
to Dimmsdale Daze,

20:48.880 --> 20:50.882
{\an3}so we brought Dimmsdale Daze
to us.

20:50.949 --> 20:53.752
- But the only way you could do
that is if you had...

20:53.819 --> 20:55.988
- [whispering]
<i>[dinging]</i>

20:56.054 --> 20:57.322
- Fairies?

20:57.389 --> 20:59.958
Ah!

21:00.025 --> 21:01.627
- That's right, fairies.

21:01.693 --> 21:03.128
- But--but wh--
- Why?

21:03.195 --> 21:05.330
{\an1}'Cause when you went all cuckoo
cray-cray last night,

21:05.397 --> 21:07.532
{\an1}you acted like such a bad mom
that your kids,

21:07.599 --> 21:08.767
who are actually your parents,

21:08.834 --> 21:10.335
qualified for fairies.

21:10.402 --> 21:11.870
- And we were available.

21:11.937 --> 21:13.839
{\an7}- Actually, I was making
a pretty penny.

21:13.905 --> 21:16.074
{\an7}crawling through doggy doors
for Slippery Pete.

21:16.141 --> 21:17.776
{\an1}Formerly known
as Lazy Eye Larry.

21:17.843 --> 21:19.878
{\an1}Yeah, he's not the best
lookout in the world.

21:19.945 --> 21:21.980
{\an3}- They got fairies
because of me?

21:22.047 --> 21:23.949
- Yeah, you kind of stunk it up.

21:24.016 --> 21:25.784
- I didn't want to be
a mean mom.

21:25.851 --> 21:28.220
I just wanted to go
to Dimmsdale Daze.

21:28.286 --> 21:30.989
Also, I'm gonna be sick.

21:31.056 --> 21:33.659
Connie, Clark, I'm so sorry.

21:33.725 --> 21:34.993
{\an3}I never should have yelled
at you

21:35.060 --> 21:37.496
{\an3}for engaging in age-appropriate
whimsy.

21:37.562 --> 21:40.032
{\an3}Being a parent is a lot harder
than I thought.

21:40.098 --> 21:42.701
{\an3}I just wish I could be
a kid again.

21:42.768 --> 21:44.536
- I think we can
make that happen.

21:44.603 --> 21:46.304
[whispering]

21:46.371 --> 21:48.040
{\an8}<i>[dinging]</i>

21:48.106 --> 21:50.776
{\an3}- I'm a kid again!
Whoopee!

21:50.842 --> 21:52.611
{\an1}- Good thing too,
'cause to be honest,

21:52.678 --> 21:54.846
you did not rock
those mom jeans.

21:54.913 --> 21:57.382
- You know, Chloe, your father
and I were talking.

21:57.449 --> 21:59.151
Well, I was talking.

21:59.217 --> 22:01.286
{\an3}- And we remembered what it was
like to be kids.

22:01.353 --> 22:03.088
- Clark, I said I was talking.
- Sorry.

22:03.155 --> 22:04.856
- Anyhoo, we remembered
what it was like

22:04.923 --> 22:06.792
to be kids and, well, we decided

22:06.858 --> 22:08.760
that you can go
to Dimmsdale Daze.

22:08.827 --> 22:10.729
- Really? Yay!

22:10.796 --> 22:12.764
{\an1}You're the most fun
parents ever.

22:12.831 --> 22:14.166
- Yeah, I wouldn't go overboard.

22:14.232 --> 22:15.901
{\an1}They're still gonna chain
themselves to a tree.

22:15.967 --> 22:18.737
- You should have some
age-appropriate whimsy.

22:18.804 --> 22:21.106
{\an3}But there are a lot of germs
at these carnivals,

22:21.173 --> 22:23.408
so just step into this
antibacterial bubble,

22:23.475 --> 22:24.810
won't you?

22:24.876 --> 22:26.812
- I'm so excited
to be a kid again.

22:26.878 --> 22:28.480
I feel so free.

22:28.547 --> 22:29.848
And antiseptic.

22:29.915 --> 22:32.584
- I'm just happy not to be
a barf bag.

22:32.651 --> 22:33.752
- This is awesome.

22:33.819 --> 22:35.554
Let's go straight
